KidOS is an Ubuntu-based operating system for primary schools.
What makes KidOS special, and why choose KidOS?
KidOS is an operating system designed for primary schools.
Our OS is user-friendly for children aged 4 to 12 and provides a safe environment for the school.
Our OS also offers unique and helpful features never before seen in an OS.
For example, KidOS includes a teacher dashboard app that gives teachers complete control over their classroom.
Within the app, they can choose what each student is allowed to do.
Other features include student monitoring, blocking certain apps,
and force-opening certain apps for students. With KidOS, we provide the ultimate experience for both students and teachers.
but only with your help can we make this come true.
